The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Sept. 24: The phaseout of the inter-state sales tax has been put on hold till next April. 

 After the implementation of value added tax (VAT), the government was supposed to phase out sales tax from this October. The finance minister today said the sales tax, now being levied at the rate of 4 per cent, was scheduled to be phased out at the rate of 1 per cent every year, but from April 2007 it will be cut at 2 per cent a year.

 Durgapur: An abandoned briefcase on the Chittaranjan Locomotive Works premises sparked a scare on Sunday evening. A bomb disposal squad was summoned from nearby Dhanbad in Jharkhand after the bag was spotted near the factorys gate No. 1. The briefcase, which has been removed to a field adjoining the factory, about 270 km from Calcutta, will be opened on Monday.

 Krishnagar: Dacoits raided the houses of three garment traders early on Sunday. Cash and jewellery worth Rs 1.4 lakh was looted from the locality at Nadias Habibpur, about 65 km from Calcutta.




